 "lrc": "[00:00.00]Beat drop, shoes tied, hood up, door slam\n[00:12.56]Still half tired but I move like a grown man\n[00:15.20]No speech, no hype, no coach in my ear\n[00:17.28]Just that old weak voice that I came here to kill\n[00:20.16]I don’t feel ready, that’s the point of it\n[00:22.16]Same cold walk, same joints feeling stiff\n[00:25.04]Gym lights buzzing, bag on the floor\n[00:27.36]I’m not in the mood, so I need it more\n[00:29.92]First set ugly, second set clean\n[00:32.48]Third set looking like I might get mean\n[00:34.88]Hands on the bar, grip chalked white\n[00:37.12]I don’t trust motivation, I trust what I write\n[00:39.84]Log book open, numbers in ink\n[00:42.08]Either add one rep or adjust how I think\n[00:44.40]I’m not here flexing, I’m not here cute\n[00:46.88]I came to tell my softer side, “shut up and move”\n[00:49.92]I keep pushing till the arms lock up\n[00:51.92]Till the lungs burn dry and the heartbeat jump\n[00:54.40]Till the sweat drip down and the vision blur\n[00:56.56]I don’t care how bad that pressure hurt\n[00:59.20]Another set, another plate, another war\n[01:01.68]Another voice in my head I ignore\n[01:04.32]If I came this far, I ain’t slowing down\n[01:06.64]I don’t stop, I don’t quit right now\n[01:09.52]Bench feel heavy, good, let it be\n[01:11.76]That’s the same weight standing between me and me\n[01:14.24]Two plates talking like, “you sure you him?”\n[01:16.80]I unrack slow with a shark-fin grin\n[01:19.28]Elbows tucked, chest tight, breath held\n[01:22.00]World get quiet when the barbell fell\n[01:24.48]Touch and press, no panic, no bounce\n[01:26.72]That’s one more reason I don’t count myself out\n[01:29.36]Squats on deck, legs already mad\n[01:31.76]But I don’t negotiate with habits I had\n[01:34.40]Deep breath, brace, spine locked in\n[01:36.88]Pain in the hole but I drive through it\n[01:38.72]Deadlift day got truth in the steel\n[01:41.36]You can’t fake heart when the knurling feel real\n[01:44.32]Bar don’t care what excuse you brought\n[01:46.40]It only moves when your whole soul talks\n[01:48.64]I keep pushing till the arms lock up\n[01:51.52]Till the lungs burn dry and the heartbeat jump\n[01:54.00]Till the sweat drip down and the vision blur\n[01:56.48]I don’t care how bad that pressure hurt\n[01:58.88]Another set, another plate, another war\n[02:01.36]Another voice in my head I ignore\n[02:04.00]If I came this far, I ain’t slowing down\n[02:06.40]I don’t stop, I don’t quit right now\n[02:09.28]Whey in the shaker, meals in the bag\n[02:11.76]Macros boring, but the mirror don’t cap\n[02:14.32]Casein late night, water all day\n[02:16.64]Stretch when I’m stiff so I don’t break\n[02:19.20]Skull crushers burn, planks make me shake\n[02:21.44]Crunches got fire running under my waist\n[02:24.32]Push-ups after, just to prove I’m sick\n[02:26.48]Not sick like ill, sick like disciplined\n[02:29.20]This ain’t about abs, this ain’t about arms\n[02:31.68]This about keeping one promise through storms\n[02:34.24]This about becoming the proof I need\n[02:36.56]When my own damn mind start testing me\n[02:39.04]No perfect week, no perfect mood\n[02:41.44]Just imperfect days where I still follow through\n[02:43.92]I don’t need applause, I don’t need a crown\n[02:46.48]I need one more rep when I wanna sit down\n[02:49.20]I keep pushing till the arms lock up\n[02:51.76]Till the lungs burn dry and the heartbeat jump\n[02:54.24]Till the sweat drip down and the vision blur\n[02:56.96]I don’t care how bad that pressure hurt\n[02:59.28]Another set, another plate, another war\n[03:01.84]Another voice in my head I ignore\n[03:04.48]If I came this far, I ain’t slowing down\n[03:06.96]I don’t stop, I don’t quit right now\n[03:09.44]I picture summer, but I don’t daydream\n[03:12.00]I put that beach body under a machine\n[03:14.56]I put that cocktail far down the road\n[03:17.12]I put today’s work where excuses go\n[03:19.44]Money right, mind right, body getting sharp\n[03:22.08]Code on the screen after reps in the dark\n[03:24.48]Not trying to be perfect, trying to be dangerous\n[03:27.52]Trying to walk in like pressure made sense\n[03:30.24]Some days I’m strong, some days I crawl\n[03:32.72]Some days just showing up wins it all\n[03:35.12]But skip too much and the old me grows\n[03:38.00]So I cut that off before it gets close\n[03:40.64]I know that voice, I know that trap\n[03:43.20]“Take one day,” then the hunger goes flat\n[03:45.84]Nah, not today, not this round\n[03:48.16]I came in tired, I leave with the crown\n[03:51.20]I keep pushing till the arms lock up\n[03:53.84]Till the lungs burn dry and the heartbeat jump\n[03:56.56]Till the sweat drip down and the vision blur\n[03:59.36]I don’t care how bad that pressure hurt\n[04:02.24]Another set, another plate, another war\n[04:04.72]Another voice in my head I ignore\n[04:07.12]If I came this far, I ain’t slowing down\n[04:10.08]I don’t stop, I don’t quit right now\n[04:13.20]No speech.\n[04:14.08]No excuse.\n[04:15.76]One more rep.\n[04:18.48]Then another.\n"
}